[2] Russia (Adygea)
Date: Fri 18 Oct 2013
Source: Adygea TV [In Russian, trans. & edited - Mod.CP]
http://www.adygtv.ru/6624/


Adygea: 11 cases of measles registered
--------------------------------------
According to the health authorities of the republic, all 11 measles infections have occurred in the Roma population.

A total of 4 of the 11 cases were unemployed adults, aged between 26 and 39 years. The other 7 were children under 14 years of age. The Health Department, in conjunction with the Center for Hygiene and Epidemiology, has initiated epidemic control measures. All contacts of the patients have been placed under surveillance.

Transmission of measles is mainly by airborne droplets. Measles is characterized by cough, coryza, and conjunctivitis. Temperature may rise to 38 degrees C [100.5 degrees F] and above at the height of the disease, accompanied by a characteristic rash.

The incubation period lasts on average about 2 weeks, in the range of 7-28 days. Vaccination against measles is the only sure way to prevent measles infection.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-RU
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The Republic of Adygea is a federal subject of Russia (a Republic) enclosed within Krasnodar Krai. Its area is 7600 square kilometres [about 2934 square miles] with a population of 439 996 (2010 census). Maykop is its capital city. A map of the Caucasus showing the location of Adygea can be accessed at http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Caucasus-political_en.svg.

Measles vaccination in Russia is well organised and almost universal, being breached mainly by migrant populations. - Mod.CP]

