[Pontardawe is a town in the Swansea Valley in south Wales. Local public health officials in South Wales have expressed disappointment and frustration at the new outbreak, which comes only 4 months after the previous outbreak -- the biggest of its kind in Wales -- hit the area and was followed by an emergency vaccination programme. - Mod.CP]

