[A large outbreak of measles in Quebec in 2011 was exceptional in that a surprisingly large number of vaccinated children who would have been expected to have been protected, developed measles. Subsequent investigation has centred on the timing of vaccination and the role of maternal antibody in determining this phenomenon. The preceding discussion comes to no final conclusion but suggests that the timing of vaccination in relation to development of protective immunity should be re-examined. - Mod.CP]

